        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 330 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Indianola, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Raiford...                        Vivian...
Hanna...                          Indianola...
Vernon...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern and northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
